; Test M73: restore both M7 mist and M8 flood after a sub turns them off,
; with M73 auto-restore set.  Re-expressed NGC-only: the classic verified the
; restore with ;py,assert this.params["_mist"/"_flood"]; gomc removed the embedded
; Python interpreter, so the restored state is surfaced as a (debug,...) comment in
; the canon trace and confirmed by the MIST_ON/FLOOD_ON calls after the sub returns.

o1000 sub
M73
M9 (mist+flood off)
o1000 endsub


m7 (mist on)
m8 (flood on)

o1000 call

(mist+flood must be on again here since restored by M73:)
(debug, _mist=#<_mist> _flood=#<_flood>)

m2
